    FromTo

    Function FromTo(from, to):
    If from < 0 or from > 99 or to < 0 or to > 99:
        Return "Invalid\n"

    Initialize an empty string result

    If from <= to:
        For i = from to to (inclusive):
            Format i as a two-digit string (with leading zero if necessary)
            Append formatted string to result
            If i is not the last number in the range:
                Append ", " to result
    Else:
        For i = from down to to (inclusive):
            Format i as a two-digit string (with leading zero if necessary)
            Append formatted string to result
            If i is not the last number in the range:
                Append ", " to result

    Append "\n" to the result

    Return result


